        section
          section
            h1 What is TypeScript?
          section
            h2 A language for large scale JavaScript development.
          section
            h2 TypeScript is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript.
          section
            img(src='assets/typescript-scopes.svg')
          section
            h2 Any browser. Any host. Any OS. Open source.
            p: a(href='https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript') github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript
        section
          section
            h1 Why should I use TypeScript?
            p: small: a(href='https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/wiki/TypeScript-Design-Goals') Design goals of TypeScript
          section
            h2 Statically identify constructs that are likely to be errors.
            p Like improved linting & errors before you run any code.
          section
            h2 Provide a structuring mechanism for larger pieces of code.
            p Module system, interfaces, imports
          section
            h2 Align with current and future ECMAScript proposals.
            p Classes, arrow functions, annotations...
          section
            h2 Preserve runtime behavior of all JavaScript code.
            p And the output is human readable.
          section
            h2 Any JavaScript code is valid TypeScript.
            p So just rename your file and get started.
          section
            h2 Tooling and developer support.
            p Helps you to get your job done.
          section
            h2 And it keeps growing
            img(src='assets/typescript-google-trends.png')
            small: a(href='https://www.google.com/trends/explore#q=TypeScript%2C%20CoffeeScript%2C%20%2Fm%2F0h52xr1%2C%20ES6&date=1%2F2011%2065m&cmpt=q&tz=Etc%2FGMT-2') Google Trends
        section
          section
            h1 Typings and definition files
          section
            h2 Definition file
            pre: code.
              /// < reference path="es6-shim.d.ts" / >

              declare var MyPoint: {
                x: number;
                y: number;
              };
          section
            h2 lib.d.ts
            p Typings for JavaScript.
          section
            h2 Typings
            p The simple way to manage and install TypeScript definitions.
            p: small: a(href='https://github.com/typings') github.com/typings
          section
            h2 Using typings
            pre: code.js.
              // Install Typings CLI utility.
              $ npm install typings --global

              // Search for definitions.
              $ typings search react

              // Install typings
              $ typings install react
            p: small: a(href='https://github.com/typings/typings#quick-start') Quick start
        section
          section
            h1 Tooling
          section
            h2 Tooling support
            ul
              li Static type checking
              li Symbol-based navigation
              li Code completion
              li Code refactoring
          section
